<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="840" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-08-24"><hi rend="italic">August 24,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1072.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 943, of the 11th instant, and to approve your note to the minister
                            for foreign affairs of that date concerning the indemnity for the
                            destruction of American missionary property at Harpoot and the conduct
                            of the Turkish authorities in connection therewith.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>